<SBODY>5 2
This <ENAMEX TYPE="EVENT.xlife">Indenture</ENAMEX>, Made the <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">Second day of January in the year eighteen hundred and ninety seven</TIMEX>
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Lisween</ENAMEX>
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Richard H. Murphy</ENAMEX>, party of the <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Village of Canandaigua</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">County of
Ontario</ENAMEX>, and <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">State of New York</ENAMEX>, by occupation a <ENAMEX TYPE="OCCUPATION">sigar - maker</ENAMEX>, party 
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Mary A. Murphy</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">his</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="FAMILYMEMBER">wife</ENAMEX>, of the <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Village of Canandaigna</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">County of Ontario</ENAMEX>, and <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">State of New York</ENAMEX>, by occupation a <ENAMEX TYPE="OCCUPATION">housewife</ENAMEX>,
of the second part
Witnesseth, That the said part of the first part, for and in consideration of the sum of
<NUMEX TYPE="MONEY">One Dollars</NUMEX>, lawful money of the <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">United States</ENAMEX>, paid by the said party of the second part, doth hereby
remise, quit claim and release
unto the said party of the second part, <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">her</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">heirs</ENAMEX> and
<ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">assigns</ENAMEX> forever,
all that tract or parcel of Land situate in the <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Village of Canandaigua</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">County of Ontario</ENAMEX>,
and <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">State of New York</ENAMEX>. Known and described as Subdivision "C" of "Parcel Fourteen"
and Subdivision "C" of "Parcel Fifteen" of the lands and premises described in
the said Judgment as the "<ENAMEX TYPE="ITE.org">Fourteenth</ENAMEX> Parcel" and as the "<ENAMEX TYPE="ITE.gpe">Fifteenth</ENAMEX> Parcel "
respectively, and being Subdivision "C" of said <ENAMEX TYPE="ITE.org">Fourteenth</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="ITE.gpe">Fifteenth</ENAMEX> Parcela-
as marked and designated on a map of the premises hereby conveyed, made 
by <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Samuel D. Backus</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="OCCUPATION">Surveyor</ENAMEX>, <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">March 5th 1895</TIMEX>, and filed with said <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE.notgpe">Referees 
Report</ENAMEX> in the Office of the <ENAMEX TYPE="OCCUPATION">Clerk</ENAMEX> of <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Ontario County</ENAMEX>. Said premises hereby 
conveyed lying and being on the west side of <ENAMEX TYPE="STRUCTURE">Adelaide Avenue</ENAMEX> in <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF.loc">said Village</ENAMEX> and being <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">about fifty seven</NUMEX> feet front and rear and about <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">One Hundred
and ninety-six</NUMEX> feet deep, as shown on said map.
The above description is taken from a deed executed by <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Thomas H. Bent</ENAMEX>
nett, as <ENAMEX TYPE="OCCUPATION">Referee</ENAMEX>, to <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Richard H. Murphy</ENAMEX>, <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">15th April, 1895</TIMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="OCCUPATION">Referee</ENAMEX> in an actions in partition in the <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Supreme Court</ENAMEX> of the <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">County of Ontario</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">N.Y.</ENAMEX> wherein-
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Sidney S. Mallory</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Clista Mallory</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">his</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="FAMILYMEMBER">wife</ENAMEX>, were <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">plaintiffs</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">George
S. Hickox</ENAMEX> and others were <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">defendants</ENAMEX>, to which action and the survey or map therein made and used, reference is hereto made.
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">LIBERTIC</ENAMEX>.
5 3
Cogether with the appurtenances and all the estate and rights of the said party of the first part, in and to the said premises.
to have and to hold the above entitled premisses unto the said party of the second part, <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">her</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">heirs</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">assigns</ENAMEX> forever.
thesaid
are by senesatwith thesaid
part of the secondpart thatthesaid part -- of theirstpartha not done
anythingherebytheabove described premises
havebeenencumberedinanywaywhatever
In Witness Whereof. The said party of the first part to these presents hath hereunto set <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">his</ENAMEX> hand and seal the <TIMEX TYPE="COREF.dat">day and year first above written</TIMEX>.
in Presence of
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Richard H. Murphy</ENAMEX> ( L.S.)
<ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">STATE OF NEW YORK</ENAMEX>,
S.
<ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">County of Ontario 
Village of Canandaigual</ENAMEX>
On this
<TIMEX TYPE="DATE">4 th day of
January in the year eighteen hundred and
ninety-seven</TIMEX>
before <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">me</ENAMEX>, the subscriber, personally appeared at <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF.loc">said Village</ENAMEX>,
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Richard H. Murphy</ENAMEX>, of the <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Village of Canandaigan</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">County of Ontario</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">State of New York</ENAMEX>,
to <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">me</ENAMEX> personally known, and known to <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">me</ENAMEX> to be the same person described in and <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">who</ENAMEX> executed the foregoing
distrument
h e
acknowledged that the executed the same
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">John S. Coe</ENAMEX>
<ENAMEX TYPE="OCCUPATION">Notary Public</ENAMEX>
A true copy of the original. Recorded this <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">4 th day of January__1897</TIMEX>, at <TIMEX TYPE="TIME">35 o'clock P. M.</TIMEX>
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">F R Hoog</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="OCCUPATION">Clerk</ENAMEX>
</SBODY>
</NBX>
